#. 2: sound
#. 3: pause (short)
#. 4: set_colour (blue)
#. 5: reset_colour
#. 6: set_colour (blue)
#. 7: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk03"
msgid ""
"<1.so><2.so>Forgive my intrusion,<3.pa> but I overheard\n"
"you speaking with the <4.se_co>elder<5.re_co>.\n"
"\n"
"It sounds like you intend to help my\n"
"husband, Teba, in the fight against\n"
"<6.se_co>Medoh<7.re_co>."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "talk04"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Is there something else you wanted\n"
"to ask?<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk05"
msgid "<1.so>Please. Now is not a good time."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
#. 3: set_colour (blue)
#. 4: reset_colour
#. 5: set_colour (blue)
#. 6: reset_colour
#. 7: sound
#. 8: set_colour (blue)
#. 9: reset_colour
#. 10: pause (longer)
msgctxt "talk06"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Teba told me everything...<2.pa>\n"
"About the <3.se_co>Flight Range<4.re_co>...\n"
"The fight with <5.se_co>Medoh<6.re_co>...\n"
"<7.so>And that <8.se_co>Medoh<9.re_co> being perched above\n"
"the village means that everything\n"
"is back to normal.\n"
"To have my husband home safe and\n"
"sound...<10.pa> I cannot begin to express my\n"
"gratitude."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: pause (short)
#. 5: choice
msgctxt "talk08"
msgid ""
"<1.so>If the <2.se_co>elder<3.re_co> trusts you,<4.pa> I will tell you\n"
"what I can.<5.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: set_colour (blue)
#. 2: sound
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk09"
msgid ""
"<1.se_co><2.so><3.re_co>Traveler...<4.pa> Please help my husband,\n"
"Teba...and our village."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
#. 3: pause (long)
#. 4: set_colour (blue)
#. 5: reset_colour
#. 6: pause (longer)
msgctxt "talk10"
msgid ""
"<1.so>My husband is very...<2.pa>impulsive.<3.pa>\n"
"Once he gets an idea in his head,\n"
"there's no reasoning with him.\n"
"We tried to stop him from going off to\n"
"fight <4.se_co>Medoh<5.re_co> on his own, but he refused\n"
"to listen.\n"
"Though I cannot feign surprise.<6.pa> I did\n"
"marry a Rito warrior, after all."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
#. 3: pause (long)
#. 4: pause (short)
#. 5: pause (short)
#. 6: pause (long)
#. 7: set_colour (red)
#. 8: reset_colour
#. 9: sound
msgctxt "talk11"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Revali is the legendary Rito warrior.<2.pa>\n"
"All the warriors here idolize him.\n"
"\n"
"My husband is no exceptionâ€”<3.pa>he is\n"
"always talking about turning our son,<4.pa>\n"
"Tulin,<5.pa> into a warrior just like Revali.\n"
"When they go and \"play\" together,<6.pa> he is\n"
"really training him at the <7.se_co>Flight Range<8.re_co>.\n"
"\n"
"<9.so>I have never wanted my sweet Tulin to \n"
"become a warrior, myself..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk15"
msgid "<1.so>Sorry, I am on my way to bed."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk16"
msgid "<1.so>Hello, <2.se_co>Champion<3.re_co> descendant."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk17"
msgid "<1.so>Good evening, <2.se_co>Champion <3.re_co>descendant."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: pause (short)
#. 4: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk19"
msgid "<1.so>Please...<2.se_co><3.pa><4.re_co>help my husband, Teba."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
msgctxt "talk20"
msgid ""
"<1.so>You met my husband?<2.pa>\n"
"Ahhh... That is a relief."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk21"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I'm happy just to hear that my husband\n"
"is still alive. It isn't much, but please\n"
"take these as thanks."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk22"
msgid ""
"<1.so>My husband left them for me to use, but\n"
"I do not want those in the house where\n"
"Tulin might play with them."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk23"
msgid "<1.so>Well..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: set_colour (red)
#. 5: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk25"
msgid ""
"<1.so>If you take off from <2.se_co>Revali's Landing<3.re_co>, it's\n"
"a straight shot down to the <4.se_co>Flight Range<5.re_co>."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: single_choice
msgctxt "talk26"
msgid ""
"<1.so>But to tell the truth, there is not much I\n"
"can do for you right now beyond telling\n"
"you where my husband went.<2.si_ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk29"
msgid "<1.so>Hello."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: text_size
#. 3: pause (short)
#. 4: text_size
msgctxt "talk30"
msgid "<1.so><2.te_si>Ahhhhh...<3.pa> Hmm...<4.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: text_size
#. 3: text_size
msgctxt "talk31"
msgid "<1.so><2.te_si>Zzz... Zzz...<3.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: text_size
#. 3: text_size
#. 4: pause (short)
#. 5: sound
#. 6: pause (longer)
#. 7: sound
msgctxt "talk35"
msgid ""
"<1.so><2.te_si>Descendant!<3.te_si>\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"Descendant!<4.pa> Are you all right?\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<5.so>My apologies...<6.pa>\n"
"I fear I have said far too much...\n"
"\n"
"<7.so>If there is anything you do not\n"
"understand, please do not hesitate to\n"
"ask."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk36"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Revali's Landing is a memorial\n"
"for the Rito Champion, Revali...\n"
"\n"
"So named in the hope that none might\n"
"forget the events of that horrible day..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
msgctxt "talk37"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I am on my way to bed.<2.pa>\n"
"We can talk later..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: set_colour (blue)
#. 4: reset_colour
#. 5: sound
#. 6: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk38"
msgid ""
"<1.so>If you need my husband, he took Tulin<2.pa>\n"
"to the <3.se_co>Flight Range<4.re_co>.\n"
"\n"
"<5.so>Now that we are at peace again,<6.pa> I would\n"
"rather they stopped doing such\n"
"dangerous training, but Teba insists."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk39"
msgid ""
"<1.so>My husband took Tulin to the\n"
"<2.se_co>Flight Range<3.re_co> again..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: sound
#. 5: set_colour (blue)
#. 6: reset_colour
#. 7: set_colour (blue)
#. 8: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk40"
msgid ""
"<1.so>My husband headed to a place called\n"
"the <2.se_co>Flight Range<3.re_co>.\n"
"\n"
"<4.so>It's in <5.se_co>Dronoc's Pass <6.re_co>at the base of \n"
"the <7.se_co>Hebra Mountains<8.re_co>."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk41"
msgid ""
"<1.so>It's a place where Rito warriors\n"
"prepare for aerial combat..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound2
#. 2: sound
#. 3: set_colour (blue)
#. 4: reset_colour
#. 5: sound
#. 6: set_colour (red)
#. 7: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk42"
msgid ""
"<1.so><2.so>I imagine he's gone there to gather\n"
"weapons for another run at <3.se_co>Medoh<4.re_co>.\n"
"\n"
"<5.so>As it happens, he made his way to the\n"
"<6.se_co>Flight Range <7.re_co>on foot this time."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
msgctxt "talk43"
msgid ""
"<1.so>He keeps saying it's to help Tulin come\n"
"of age as a warrior or something.<2.pa>\n"
"But Tulin's still a fledgling..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk44"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I just...<2.pa>do not want Tulin to lose his\n"
"innocence too early. He is such a sweet\n"
"boy."
msgstr ""

